  Licensed under the MIT License

Each ``<name>.html`` / ``<name>.md`` pair derives from a
``<div class="case" data-name="…">`` block in turndown's harness:
the input is the case's ``<input>`` HTML, and the expected output
is the matching ``<output>`` text. Cases with non-default
``data-options`` (e.g. ``linkStyle: 'referenced'``,
``codeBlockStyle: 'fenced'``) are included for completeness but are
not exercised by our converter and are listed in
``tests/test_fixtures.py`` under ``KNOWN_FAILURES``.

